NeoVimChad(turns neovim into a more IDE experience, linter/syntax highlighting for many different languages):
https://nvchad.com/
https://github.com/NvChad/NvChad
One Liner:
git clone https://github.com/NvChad/NvChad ~/.config/nvim --depth 1 && nvim
Personalize Theme: <space> + T + H
Find Files Menu: <space> + F + F
Find Open Files in buffers: <space> + F + B  / tab to go forward / shift + tab to go backwards / close : <space> + x
NVIM Tree Shows a file tree: <Ctrl> + N
Rename: R
Copy: C
Paste: P
Delete: D
Mark: M
Vertical split: :VSP
Horizontal Split: :SP
To Navigate: Ctrl + HJKL = Ctrl +K (up) / Ctrl+ H (Down) 
CheatSheet : <space> + C + H
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yW3ovyQCwpw&ab_channel=MentalOutlaw
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Mtgo-nP_r8Y&ab_channel=DreamsofCode
# Linux / Macos (unix) Uninstall:
rm -rf ~/.config/nvim
rm -rf ~/.local/share/nvim

